mt-0 mt-0.5 [&amp;_p:last-child]:mb-0"><p>You must enable billing on your G=
oogle Cloud project, as a valid billing account is required for streaming i=
nserts.</p></div></div><h4 id=3D"setting-up-bigquery-service-account" class=
=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Setting up BigQuery Service Account<a href=3D"https=
://supabase.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introduction#setting-=
up-bigquery-service-account" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 g=
roup-hover:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a><=
/h4><p>The service account used must have sufficient permissions to insert =
into your Google Cloud BigQuery. Ensure that the service account has either=
:</p><ul>
<li>BigQuery Admin role; or</li>
<li>The following permissions:<!-- -->
<ul>
<li><code>bigquery.datasets.create</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.datasets.get</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.datasets.getIamPolicy</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.datasets.update</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.jobs.create</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.routines.create</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.routines.update</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.tables.create</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.tables.delete</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.tables.get</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.tables.getData</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.tables.update</code></li>
<li><code>bigquery.tables.updateData</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul><p>You can create the service account via the web console or <code>gcl=
oud</code> CLI, as per the <a href=3D"https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/key=
s-create-delete">Google Cloud documentation</a>. In the web console, you ca=
n create the key by navigating to IAM &gt; Service Accounts &gt; Actions (d=
ropdown) &gt; Manage Keys</p><p>We recommend setting the BigQuery Admin rol=
e, as it simplifies permissions setup.</p><h4 id=3D"download-the-service-ac=
count-keys" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Download the Service Account Keys<=
a href=3D"https://supabase.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introd=
uction#download-the-service-account-keys" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-=
2 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">=
#</span></a></h4><p>After the service account is created, you will need to =
create a key for the service account. This key will sign the JWTs for API r=
equests that the Analytics server makes with BigQuery. This can be done thr=
ough the IAM section in Google Cloud console.</p><h4 id=3D"docker-image-con=
figuration" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Docker Image Configuration<a href=
=3D"https://supabase.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introduction=
#docker-image-configuration" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 g=
roup-hover:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a><=
/h4><p>Using the example <a href=3D"https://github.com/supabase/supabase/tr=
ee/master/docker">self-hosting stack based on docker-compose</a>, you inclu=
de the logging related services using the following command</p><ol>
<li>Update the <code>.env.example</code> file with the necessary environmen=
t variables.</li>
</ol><ul>
<li><code>GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID</code></li>
<li><code>GOOGLE_PROJECT_NUMBER</code></li>
</ul><ol start=3D"2">
<li>Place your Service Account key in your present working directory with t=
he filename <code>gcloud.json</code>.</li>
<li>On <code>docker-compose.yml</code>, uncomment the block section below t=
he commentary <code># Uncomment to use Big Query backend for analytics</cod=
e></li>
<li>On <code>docker-compose.yml</code>, comment the block section below the=
 commentary <code># Comment variables to use Big Query backend for analytic=
s</code></li>
</ol><p>Thereafter, you can start the example stack using the following com=
mand:</p><div class=3D"ch-codeblock not-prose " data-ch-theme=3D"supabase">=
<div class=3D"ch-code-wrapper ch-code" data-ch-measured=3D"true"><code clas=
