tset-storage-location" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 group-h=
over:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a></h4><p=
>Currently, all BigQuery datasets stored and managed by Analytics, whether =
via CLI or self-hosted, will default to the US region.</p><h2 id=3D"vector-=
usage" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Vector Usage<a href=3D"https://supabase=
.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introduction#vector-usage" aria-=
hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition"=
><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a></h2><p>In the Docker Compose examp=
le, Vector is used for the logging pipieline, where log events are forwarde=
d to the Analytics API for ingestion.</p><p>Please refer to the <a href=3D"=
https://github.com/supabase/supabase/blob/master/docker/volumes/logs/vector=
.yml">Vector configuration file</a> when customizing your own setup.</p><p>=
You <strong>must</strong> ensure that the payloads matches the expected eve=
nt schema structure. Without the correct structure, it would cause the Stud=
io Logs UI features to break.</p><h2 id=3D"differences-from-platform" class=
=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Differences from Platform<a href=3D"https://supabas=
e.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introduction#differences-from-p=
latform" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-1=
00 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a></h2><p>API logs rely=
 on Kong instead of the Supabase Cloud API Gateway. Logs from Kong are not =
enriched with platform-only data.</p><p>Within the self-hosted setup, all l=
ogs are routed to Logflare via Vector. As Kong routes API requests to Postg=
REST, self-hosted or local deployments will result in Kong request logs ins=
tead.
This would result in differences in the log event metadata between self-hos=
ted API requests and Supabase Platform requests.</p><h2 id=3D"production-re=
commendations" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Production Recommendations<a hr=
ef=3D"https://supabase.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introducti=
on#production-recommendations" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0=
 group-hover:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a=
></h2><p>To self-host in a production setting, we recommend performing the =
following for a better experience.</p><h3 id=3D"ensure-that-logflare-is-beh=
ind-a-firewall-and-restrict-all-network-access-to-it-besides-safe-requests"=
 class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Ensure that Logflare is behind a firewall and=
 restrict all network access to it besides safe requests.<a href=3D"https:/=
/supabase.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introduction#ensure-tha=
t-logflare-is-behind-a-firewall-and-restrict-all-network-access-to-it-besid=
es-safe-requests" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 group-hover:=
opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</span></a></h3><p>Self=
-hosted Logflare has UI authentication disabled and is intended for exposur=
e to the internet. We recommend restricting access to the dashboard, access=
ible at the <code>/dashboard</code> path.
If dashboard access is required for managing sources, we recommend having a=
n authentication layer, such as a VPN.</p><h3 id=3D"use-a-different-postgre=
s-database-to-store-logflare-data" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Use a diffe=
rent Postgres Database to store Logflare data.<a href=3D"https://supabase.c=
om/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/introduction#use-a-different-postg=
res-database-to-store-logflare-data" aria-hidden=3D"true" class=3D"ml-2 opa=
city-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=3D"true">#</sp=
an></a></h3><p>Logflare requires a Postgres database to function. However, =
if there is an issue with you self-hosted Postgres service, you would not b=
e able to debug it as it would also bring Logflare down together.</p><p>The=
 self-hosted example is only used as a minimal example on running the entir=
e stack, however it is not recommended to use the same database server for =
both production and observability.</p><h3 id=3D"use-big-query-as-the-logfla=
re-backend" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Use Big Query as the Logflare Back=
end<a href=3D"https://supabase.com/docs/reference/self-hosting-analytics/in=
troduction#use-big-query-as-the-logflare-backend" aria-hidden=3D"true" clas=
s=3D"ml-2 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition"><span aria-hidden=
=3D"true">#</span></a></h3><p>The current Postgres Ingestion backend isn't =
optimized for production usage. We recommend using Big Query for more heavy=
 use cases.</p><p><strong>We recommend using the BigQuery backend for produ=
ction environments as it offers better scaling and querying/debugging exper=
iences.</strong></p></div><div class=3D"w-full min-w-full sticky top-32 sel=
f-start"><h3 id=3D"client-libraries" class=3D"group scroll-mt-24">Client li=
